### Package structure
packages/oauth/
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts              ← Public API barrel (all exports)
│   ├── client.ts             ← OAuthClient class
│   ├── types.ts              ← All TypeScript types + ServiceAdapter interface
│   ├── pkce.ts               ← generatePKCE, generateVerifier, computeChallenge
│   ├── adapters/
│   │   ├── base.ts           ← BaseServiceAdapter (fetch-based, no axios)
│   │   ├── google.ts         ← GoogleAdapter (access_type=offline, scope prefix, PKCE)
│   │   ├── github.ts         ← GitHubAdapter (Accept: json, comma scopes, DELETE revoke)
│   │   ├── slack.ts          ← SlackAdapter (comma scopes, authed_user, Bearer revoke)
│   │   ├── notion.ts         ← NotionAdapter (Basic auth exchange, no-op revoke)
│   │   ├── salesforce.ts     ← SalesforceAdapter (instance_url, sandbox config)
│   │   └── index.ts          ← Barrel + createAdapter() factory
│   └── middleware/
│       └── express.ts        ← credOAuth() Express middleware
└── src/__tests__/
    ├── pkce.test.ts          ← 10 tests
    ├── adapters.test.ts      ← 25 tests
    ├── client.test.ts        ← 13 tests
    └── middleware.test.ts    ← 6 tests

### Results
- 54 tests passing, 0 failing
- Dual CJS + ESM output in dist/
- TypeScript declarations in dist/types/
- Zero runtime dependencies (fetch + crypto built-ins only)
- state = crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('hex')
- PKCE = base64url(sha256(verifier)), method S256

### Key constraints met
- ZERO runtime deps ✓
- state uses crypto.randomBytes ✓
- Google: access_type=offline, prompt=consent, scope prefix normalization ✓
- Slack: comma scopes, no PKCE, no refresh (throws), nested authed_user, Bearer revocation ✓
- Notion: Basic auth header, no PKCE, no refresh (throws), no-op revoke ✓
- GitHub: Accept: application/json, comma scopes, DELETE+Basic revoke, 404=success ✓
- Salesforce: instance_url in response, PKCE, sandbox config ✓
- Express middleware with CSRF state validation ✓
- README > 1000 chars ✓
- packages/oauth added to root workspaces ✓
